1
00:00:05,506 --> 00:00:06,548
<b>[HAKUSHI]
Wrong.</b>

2
00:00:06,590 --> 00:00:09,217
<b>[YUKI struggling]</b>

3
00:00:09,259 --> 00:00:10,511
<b>Kill him first?</b>

4
00:00:10,552 --> 00:00:11,595
<b>[HAKUSHI]
Wrong.</b>

5
00:00:11,637 --> 00:00:13,848
<b>[YUKI grunting, panting]</b>

6
00:00:13,889 --> 00:00:15,599
<b>Play dead, then?</b>

7
00:00:15,641 --> 00:00:16,684
<b>[HAKUSHI]
Wrong.</b>

8
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,769
<b>[YUKI grunting, panting]</b>

9
00:00:22,021 --> 00:00:23,398
<b>[confused gasp]</b>

10
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:24,984
<b>[cries out]</b>

11
00:00:25,024 --> 00:00:28,069
<b>[struggling]</b>

12
00:00:31,866 --> 00:00:36,161
<b>[HAKUSHI] The right answer is
"avoid psychos," always.</b>

13
00:00:39,748 --> 00:00:41,834
<b>[YUKI]
I'm confused.</b>

14
00:00:41,876 --> 00:00:45,379
<b>Every game I played
so far, I killed people,</b>

15
00:00:45,420 --> 00:00:48,382
<b>and I'm not talking
just one or two.</b>

16
00:00:48,423 --> 00:00:52,093
<b>So doesn't that
make me a psycho?</b>

17
00:00:52,135 --> 00:00:55,764
<b>I'm pretty sure folks out in
society would see it that way.</b>

18
00:00:57,892 --> 00:00:59,351
<b>[HAKUSHI] Winning one
of these death games</b>

19
00:00:59,393 --> 00:01:01,520
<b>doesn't depend on killing.</b>

20
00:01:01,562 --> 00:01:04,023
<b>It depends on surviving
to the end.</b>

21
00:01:05,148 --> 00:01:06,859
<b>And that's the reason
I've been pushing you</b>

22
00:01:06,901 --> 00:01:09,778
<b>so hard to be
a pro at surviving.</b>

23
00:01:09,820 --> 00:01:12,573
<b>But a homicidal
maniac's different.</b>

24
00:01:14,867 --> 00:01:16,451
<b>They don't play death
games to win</b>

25
00:01:16,493 --> 00:01:18,954
<b>and get paid,
so don't fight 'em.</b>

26
00:01:18,996 --> 00:01:20,247
<b>Avoid 'em.</b>

27
00:01:24,585 --> 00:01:26,795
<b>[YUKI] What if
I don't have a choice?</b>

28
00:01:26,837 --> 00:01:30,841
<b>What if the only way to win
is to go head-to-head</b>

29
00:01:30,883 --> 00:01:33,176
<b>with a psycho killer?</b>

30
00:01:33,218 --> 00:01:35,262
<b>How am I supposed
to handle that?</b>

31
00:01:39,307 --> 00:01:41,309
<b>[HAKUSHI] You'll have
to figure that out.</b>

32
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:44,730
<b>Your training's over now.</b>

33
00:01:44,772 --> 00:01:48,400
<b>[distant struggling, gasping]</b>

34
00:01:50,069 --> 00:01:51,904
<b>[YUKI] The psycho
Hakushi just warned</b>

35
00:01:51,946 --> 00:01:57,451
<b>us about was probably the one
that threw the pine cone.</b>

36
00:01:57,492 --> 00:02:00,119
<b>But then, that means
the killer followed</b>

37
00:02:00,161 --> 00:02:03,373
<b>her all the way back here.</b>

38
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:06,418
<b>No way.</b>

39
00:02:06,460 --> 00:02:09,212
<b>She'd never screw up like that.</b>

40
00:02:11,715 --> 00:02:14,551
<b>Or did she?</b>

41
00:02:14,593 --> 00:02:18,055
<b>Was there any other
way to explain it?</b>

42
00:02:18,097 --> 00:02:21,475
<b>[gentle music]</b>

43
00:02:21,516 --> 00:02:28,732
<b>♪ ♪</b>

44
00:02:31,819 --> 00:02:33,570
<b>No.</b>

45
00:02:33,612 --> 00:02:37,282
<b>The why and how of it
didn't matter anymore.</b>

46
00:02:38,659 --> 00:02:43,747
<b>Right now, the one thing
I needed to focus on,</b>

47
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:47,417
<b>the only thing,</b>

48
00:02:51,046 --> 00:02:52,631
<b>was surviving.</b>

49
00:02:52,673 --> 00:02:54,382
<b>[static]</b>

50
00:02:56,802 --> 00:03:01,723
<b>[pensive music]</b>

51
00:03:01,765 --> 00:03:09,064
<b>♪ ♪</b>

52
00:03:11,650 --> 00:03:13,819
<b>[gasps softly]</b>

53
00:03:13,861 --> 00:03:15,946
<b>A-chan?</b>

54
00:03:20,408 --> 00:03:22,201
<b>[laughs]</b>

55
00:03:24,997 --> 00:03:29,626
<b>[YOUNG AIRI] What'll happen
to me if I don't become a swan?</b>

56
00:03:29,668 --> 00:03:30,961
<b>[AIRI'S MOM]
What?</b>

57
00:03:36,591 --> 00:03:38,969
<b>[YOUNG AIRI]
I'm a duck now,</b>

58
00:03:40,721 --> 00:03:42,890
<b>but when I grow up,</b>

59
00:03:44,391 --> 00:03:46,894
<b>and I don't get
to be a swan,</b>

60
00:03:49,563 --> 00:03:53,650
<b>what do I do if
I'm still a duck then?</b>

61
00:03:53,692 --> 00:03:55,360
<b>[gasps softly]</b>

62
00:03:57,236 --> 00:03:58,488
<b>Hm.</b>

63
00:04:00,824 --> 00:04:02,409
<b>I don't know.</b>

64
00:04:02,450 --> 00:04:05,286
<b>What do you think
you should do?</b>

65
00:04:05,328 --> 00:04:07,748
<b>[YOUNG AIRI]
If I stay a duck?</b>

66
00:04:08,999 --> 00:04:10,417
<b>Mmm.</b>

67
00:04:11,210 --> 00:04:13,045
<b>I don't know.</b>

68
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:26,683
<b>I think swans
are pretty neat,</b>

69
00:04:26,725 --> 00:04:29,937
<b>but I like ducks more.</b>

70
00:04:30,771 --> 00:04:34,191
<b>[chuckles] Oh, yeah?</b>

71
00:04:36,443 --> 00:04:37,736
<b>Then don't worry.</b>

72
00:04:37,778 --> 00:04:40,363
<b>Even if you stay
a duck, you'll be fine.</b>

73
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:44,159
<b>[chuckles]</b>

74
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:55,503
<b>Even if I don't grow
up to be a swan,</b>

75
00:04:58,548 --> 00:05:00,467
<b>and even if...</b>

76
00:05:01,593 --> 00:05:03,929
<b>I can't change
that fact,</b>

77
00:05:07,390 --> 00:05:08,725
<b>still,</b>

78
00:05:10,144 --> 00:05:12,187
<b>what else is there?</b>

79
00:05:12,229 --> 00:05:14,606
<b>[sniffling, crying]</b>

80
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:18,986
<b>[distant banging]</b>

81
00:05:24,992 --> 00:05:30,371
<b>I have to keep
trying and fighting.</b>

82
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:41,300
<b>[pleasant but distorted music]</b>

83
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:44,761
<b>♪ ♪</b>

84
00:05:44,803 --> 00:05:47,514
<b>[ANNOUNCER]
Everyone, time to head back.</b>

85
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:49,266
<b>It's almost 5:00 PM,</b>

86
00:05:49,308 --> 00:05:52,769
<b>which means
day one is just about over.</b>

87
00:05:52,811 --> 00:05:59,109
<b>♪ ♪</b>

88
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:05,448
<b>Everyone, time to head back.</b>

89
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,284
<b>It's almost 5:00 PM,</b>

90
00:06:07,326 --> 00:06:10,704
<b>which means
day one is just about over.</b>

91
00:06:10,745 --> 00:06:16,793
<b>♪ ♪</b>

92
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:26,427
<b>[MOEGI] He couldn't
get closer to the Sun,</b>

93
00:06:26,469 --> 00:06:30,015
<b>no matter how far
or high he flew.</b>

94
00:06:31,558 --> 00:06:32,851
<b>[gunshots]</b>

95
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:35,062
<b>The Sun just seemed
to grow smaller</b>

96
00:06:35,103 --> 00:06:37,480
<b>and get further away.</b>

97
00:06:37,522 --> 00:06:39,566
<b>Then the Sun said,</b>

98
00:06:42,069 --> 00:06:44,612
<b>"You are a Night hawk, yes?"</b>

99
00:06:45,404 --> 00:06:49,117
<b>Ah, this must be hard for you.</b>

100
00:06:50,451 --> 00:06:51,953
<b>Wait for night.</b>

101
00:06:51,995 --> 00:06:55,999
<b>Then fly up to the stars
and speak with them.</b>

102
00:06:57,376 --> 00:07:01,713
<b>After all, you are
not a daytime bird."</b>

103
00:07:01,755 --> 00:07:03,131
<b>[pants, grunts]</b>

104
00:07:03,173 --> 00:07:06,467
<b>[breathing heavily]</b>

105
00:07:08,095 --> 00:07:09,388
<b>[HIKAWA]
Moegi!</b>

106
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:13,683
<b>[ANNOUNCER] Everyone,
time to head back.</b>

107
00:07:13,725 --> 00:07:14,851
<b>You're alive.</b>

108
00:07:14,893 --> 00:07:16,103
<b>Thank goodness.</b>

109
00:07:17,312 --> 00:07:19,314
<b>There's a serial
killer on Team Bunny,</b>

110
00:07:19,356 --> 00:07:22,150
<b>so now there's more to worry
about than our kill quota.</b>

111
00:07:23,568 --> 00:07:25,612
<b>Are you heading back?</b>

112
00:07:25,653 --> 00:07:26,905
<b>No.</b>

113
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:31,534
<b>I'm, like, lucky
I ran into you.</b>

114
00:07:31,576 --> 00:07:33,452
<b>I was all alone.</b>

115
00:07:33,494 --> 00:07:35,705
<b>Let's stick together
from now on.</b>

116
00:07:35,747 --> 00:07:38,292
<b>That way, we can survive.</b>

117
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:39,042
<b>'Kay.</b>

118
00:07:40,377 --> 00:07:45,506
<b>By the way, I hate to ask,
but I need a favor, sort of.</b>

119
00:07:46,591 --> 00:07:50,178
<b>I'm, like, all out
of ammo for this thing.</b>

120
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:54,182
<b>If you have a bullet or two
to spare, I'd appreciate it.</b>

121
00:07:54,975 --> 00:07:56,517
<b>Sure.</b>

122
00:07:57,269 --> 00:07:58,937
<b>[HIKAWA]
You're a lifesaver.</b>

123
00:08:05,152 --> 00:08:07,112
<b>[MOEGI]
I can spare one bullet.</b>

124
00:08:08,363 --> 00:08:09,572
<b>[synthesized clock chiming]</b>

125
00:08:09,614 --> 00:08:12,159
<b>[ANNOUNCER]
It's 5:00 PM now.</b>

126
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:16,746
<b>The gates will open again
for everyone at 6:00 AM.</b>

127
00:08:22,752 --> 00:08:24,712
<b>It's 5:00 PM now.</b>

128
00:08:24,754 --> 00:08:28,925
<b>The gates will open again
for everyone at 6:00 AM.</b>

129
00:08:28,967 --> 00:08:36,266
<b>♪ ♪</b>

130
00:08:42,105 --> 00:08:44,607
<b>[MOEGI]
I ran into a rabbit.</b>

131
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:53,700
<b>She was pale, like a ghost.</b>

132
00:08:55,452 --> 00:08:58,330
<b>[cacophonous music]</b>

133
00:08:58,372 --> 00:09:05,670
<b>♪ ♪</b>

134
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:09,174
<b>[static]</b>

135
00:09:10,425 --> 00:09:14,137
<b>[frantic flapping, chittering]</b>

136
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:19,726
<b>[ominous music]</b>

137
00:09:19,767 --> 00:09:26,649
<b>♪ ♪</b>

138
00:09:33,407 --> 00:09:35,283
<b>[cawing]</b>

139
00:09:35,325 --> 00:09:40,497
<b>♪ ♪</b>

140
00:09:40,539 --> 00:09:41,456
<b>[gasps]</b>

141
00:09:41,498 --> 00:09:48,587
<b>♪ ♪</b>

142
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:54,219
<b>[flapping fades out]</b>

143
00:09:54,261 --> 00:10:01,560
<b>♪ ♪</b>

144
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:07,190
<b>[flapping, chittering]</b>

145
00:10:07,232 --> 00:10:14,531
<b>♪ ♪</b>

146
00:10:18,785 --> 00:10:19,827
<b>[exhales nervously]</b>

147
00:10:19,869 --> 00:10:22,747
<b>[gentle music]</b>

148
00:10:22,789 --> 00:10:30,088
<b>♪ ♪</b>

149
00:10:38,597 --> 00:10:39,931
<b>[gasps softly]</b>

150
00:10:39,973 --> 00:10:46,980
<b>♪ ♪</b>

151
00:10:52,735 --> 00:10:54,946
<b>[gasps]</b>

152
00:10:56,156 --> 00:10:58,116
<b>[ominous music]</b>

153
00:10:58,158 --> 00:11:01,620
<b>♪ ♪</b>

154
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:02,912
<b>What?</b>

155
00:11:03,955 --> 00:11:05,790
<b>[gasps]</b>

156
00:11:05,832 --> 00:11:08,835
<b>♪ ♪</b>

157
00:11:08,876 --> 00:11:12,130
<b>[struggling]</b>

158
00:11:12,172 --> 00:11:15,674
<b>[tense music]</b>

159
00:11:15,716 --> 00:11:18,637
<b>♪ ♪</b>

160
00:11:18,677 --> 00:11:19,929
<b>[gunshot]</b>

161
00:11:20,679 --> 00:11:22,349
<b>[gasping]</b>

162
00:11:23,099 --> 00:11:26,769
<b>[kicking]</b>

163
00:11:27,521 --> 00:11:29,230
<b>[grunting]</b>

164
00:11:29,272 --> 00:11:30,231
<b>[cries out]</b>

165
00:11:30,273 --> 00:11:34,152
<b>[panting]</b>

166
00:11:34,194 --> 00:11:37,280
<b>[MOEGI screaming angrily]</b>

167
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:43,620
<b>[tumbling, panting]</b>

168
00:11:46,289 --> 00:11:47,248
<b>[growls]</b>

169
00:11:47,290 --> 00:11:48,500
<b>[gunshot]</b>

170
00:11:48,542 --> 00:11:55,089
<b>♪ ♪</b>

171
00:12:00,261 --> 00:12:03,306
<b>She had way more
experience than me.</b>

172
00:12:04,765 --> 00:12:09,145
<b>No matter what I did, the ghost
was always one step ahead.</b>

173
00:12:09,187 --> 00:12:12,773
<b>And now I'm her target!</b>

174
00:12:13,608 --> 00:12:15,734
<b>[cawing]</b>

175
00:12:18,321 --> 00:12:21,032
<b>I thought if I
killed my folks--</b>

176
00:12:22,116 --> 00:12:25,161
<b>[somber music]</b>

177
00:12:25,203 --> 00:12:27,664
<b>♪ ♪</b>

178
00:12:27,706 --> 00:12:32,293
<b>I thought if I could just kill
my folks, then--</b>

179
00:12:32,335 --> 00:12:33,294
<b>then--</b>

180
00:12:33,336 --> 00:12:34,504
<b>[sobs]</b>

181
00:12:34,546 --> 00:12:38,258
<b>I could be strong, like Kyara.</b>

182
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:40,510
<b>[gunshots]</b>

183
00:12:40,552 --> 00:12:43,762
<b>♪ ♪</b>

184
00:12:43,804 --> 00:12:49,852
<b>I knew it was impossible,
a nighthawk becoming a whale.</b>

185
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:52,355
<b>Yeah, right.</b>

186
00:12:52,397 --> 00:12:53,565
<b>That's not--</b>

187
00:12:53,607 --> 00:12:55,233
<b>[sobs]</b>

188
00:12:55,275 --> 00:12:56,943
<b>I could never be.</b>

189
00:12:56,984 --> 00:13:00,363
<b>[crying]</b>

190
00:13:01,573 --> 00:13:04,325
<b>[KYARA exhales]</b>

191
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:07,495
<b>I love you.
[inhales]</b>

192
00:13:08,580 --> 00:13:10,039
<b>[MOEGI] That's what
she thought Kyara</b>

193
00:13:10,081 --> 00:13:14,168
<b>meant with each deep
breath she took.</b>

194
00:13:16,003 --> 00:13:17,964
<b>[KYARA]
I love you.</b>

195
00:13:19,132 --> 00:13:21,551
<b>[MOEGI] No one ever
held her like that</b>

196
00:13:21,593 --> 00:13:24,512
<b>or made her feel
like that before.</b>

197
00:13:25,804 --> 00:13:29,850
<b>So she didn't really
understand what it was then.</b>

198
00:13:35,106 --> 00:13:37,108
<b>[KYARA]
I love you.</b>

199
00:13:38,443 --> 00:13:41,946
<b>[MOEGI]
But that warm feeling she got</b>

200
00:13:41,988 --> 00:13:47,118
<b>was the only reason she
needed to keep on living.</b>

201
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:50,747
<b>[deep breathing]</b>

202
00:13:50,789 --> 00:13:56,544
<b>Like that nighthawk
trying to reach that star.</b>

203
00:13:58,963 --> 00:14:00,256
<b>I--</b>

204
00:14:01,924 --> 00:14:05,470
<b>I have to keep
trying and fighting.</b>

205
00:14:08,807 --> 00:14:12,435
<b>I refuse to die here.</b>

206
00:14:14,228 --> 00:14:18,525
<b>I refuse to die
because Kyara is my teacher!</b>

207
00:14:18,566 --> 00:14:20,318
<b>[clattering]</b>

208
00:14:22,654 --> 00:14:24,614
<b>[smoke releases]</b>

209
00:14:24,656 --> 00:14:27,575
<b>[gasps softly]</b>

210
00:14:27,617 --> 00:14:30,537
<b>[gasping nervously]</b>

211
00:14:30,578 --> 00:14:31,870
<b>[gunshots]</b>

212
00:14:31,912 --> 00:14:33,832
<b>[gasps]</b>

213
00:14:37,001 --> 00:14:41,798
<b>[MOEGI] A white-hot pain burned
through every nerve in my body.</b>

214
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,466
<b>[soft piano music]</b>

215
00:14:43,508 --> 00:14:47,554
<b>I took a shot
to my stomach, my shoulder,</b>

216
00:14:47,595 --> 00:14:51,057
<b>and maybe one other place.</b>

217
00:14:51,098 --> 00:14:53,434
<b>I didn't know exactly
where anymore.</b>

218
00:14:53,476 --> 00:14:57,938
<b>♪ ♪</b>

219
00:14:57,980 --> 00:15:00,650
<b>That ghostly girl made a face.</b>

220
00:15:00,692 --> 00:15:04,362
<b>I couldn't tell if she liked
killing me or hated it.</b>

221
00:15:04,404 --> 00:15:05,864
<b>[gun cocks]</b>

222
00:15:08,825 --> 00:15:10,993
<b>I guess it didn't matter.</b>

223
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:13,371
<b>I was done either way.</b>

224
00:15:16,541 --> 00:15:19,001
<b>And if this was
the end for me,</b>

225
00:15:19,043 --> 00:15:21,128
<b>it meant I didn't
have to pretend</b>

226
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:23,381
<b>to be strong anymore.</b>

227
00:15:25,174 --> 00:15:28,762
<b>I haven't felt like this
since I killed my folks.</b>

228
00:15:33,307 --> 00:15:35,059
<b>I forget.</b>

229
00:15:35,101 --> 00:15:41,357
<b>At the end of that story, what
happened to that nighthawk?</b>

230
00:15:42,734 --> 00:15:45,570
<b>Did it become a star?</b>

231
00:15:46,696 --> 00:15:49,824
<b>[sighs]</b>

232
00:15:49,866 --> 00:15:51,743
<b>Oh, well.</b>

233
00:15:51,785 --> 00:15:55,329
<b>I'll ask Kyara to read
it to me again.</b>

234
00:15:57,998 --> 00:16:02,503
<b>Anyway, until my last breath,</b>

235
00:16:02,545 --> 00:16:04,422
<b>I, Moegi--</b>

236
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:06,173
<b>[flapping]</b>

237
00:16:06,215 --> 00:16:09,552
<b>[chirping]</b>

238
00:16:09,594 --> 00:16:16,643
<b>spent my very last moments--</b>

239
00:16:17,811 --> 00:16:21,230
<b>[crying]</b>

240
00:16:21,980 --> 00:16:26,402
<b>Crying in frustration.</b>

241
00:16:26,444 --> 00:16:29,781
<b>[cawing]</b>

242
00:16:29,823 --> 00:16:36,704
<b>♪ ♪</b>

243
00:17:07,652 --> 00:17:11,364
<b>[chirping]</b>

244
00:17:19,037 --> 00:17:25,085
<b>"The nighthawk's star burned
on and continued to burn.</b>

245
00:17:27,463 --> 00:17:33,970
<b>It kept burning
and burning and burning."</b>

246
00:17:34,012 --> 00:17:37,264
<b>[flapping, chirping]</b>

247
00:17:38,516 --> 00:17:43,103
<b>"And still,
to this day, it burns."</b>

248
00:17:43,145 --> 00:17:46,774
<b>[water flowing]</b>

249
00:17:56,325 --> 00:18:00,078
<b>[YUKI] That Stump
wasn't even a threat.</b>

250
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:02,665
<b>She had no talent for this.</b>

251
00:18:02,707 --> 00:18:05,001
<b>That's all there was to say.</b>

252
00:18:06,627 --> 00:18:10,423
<b>It seems the psycho
killer was her mentor.</b>

253
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:15,428
<b>[chuckles] She wasn't a very
good student, honestly.</b>

254
00:18:15,469 --> 00:18:20,433
<b>Even if they'd done this
over and over a hundred times,</b>

255
00:18:20,474 --> 00:18:23,937
<b>that Stump would have
lost every single time.</b>

256
00:18:23,978 --> 00:18:25,521
<b>She was that hopeless.</b>

257
00:18:25,563 --> 00:18:28,441
<b>[footsteps]</b>

258
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:33,947
<b>Still, she saw it clear as day.</b>

259
00:18:35,573 --> 00:18:38,576
<b>The look on her
face as she died--</b>

260
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:41,287
<b>she looked like
someone who poured</b>

261
00:18:41,328 --> 00:18:43,081
<b>her heart and soul
into something</b>

262
00:18:43,121 --> 00:18:48,086
<b>and still, somehow, failed.</b>

263
00:18:48,126 --> 00:18:51,129
<b>Here's this poor girl
who lived life as best</b>

264
00:18:51,171 --> 00:18:53,925
<b>she could and still lost.</b>

265
00:18:53,967 --> 00:18:56,510
<b>What does she get
for that when it's over?</b>

266
00:18:56,552 --> 00:19:00,264
<b>[scoffs]
Nothing-- that's what.</b>

267
00:19:00,306 --> 00:19:03,601
<b>The Stump girl's expression
was a mystery to Yuki.</b>

268
00:19:03,643 --> 00:19:06,104
<b>Even if you told her
what it was about,</b>

269
00:19:06,144 --> 00:19:09,231
<b>she still wouldn't be
able to sympathize.</b>

270
00:19:10,316 --> 00:19:14,070
<b>Still, there was
something there.</b>

271
00:19:15,237 --> 00:19:17,782
<b>It was different from
Yuki's weak reasons</b>

272
00:19:17,824 --> 00:19:20,242
<b>for playing death games.</b>

273
00:19:20,284 --> 00:19:23,496
<b>Stump girl wasn't one of those
"one-and-done type" players.</b>

274
00:19:23,537 --> 00:19:24,998
<b>She played because
she was reaching</b>

275
00:19:25,039 --> 00:19:26,666
<b>for something bigger than her,</b>

276
00:19:26,707 --> 00:19:29,627
<b>something she thought
she could achieve.</b>

277
00:19:29,669 --> 00:19:30,920
<b>She had a goal.</b>

278
00:19:30,962 --> 00:19:34,548
<b>[lights clicking on]</b>

279
00:19:37,051 --> 00:19:38,511
<b>And Yuki...</b>

280
00:19:40,387 --> 00:19:43,057
<b>she killed it dead.</b>

281
00:19:47,145 --> 00:19:51,858
<b>A girl, drifting through life--</b>

282
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:53,651
<b>killed it.</b>

283
00:19:55,277 --> 00:19:59,615
<b>No, not someone alive.</b>

284
00:19:59,657 --> 00:20:03,619
<b>Someone dead, a ghost.</b>

285
00:20:04,871 --> 00:20:08,624
<b>A ghost stopped it
from happening</b>

286
00:20:08,666 --> 00:20:11,460
<b>with her skills,</b>

287
00:20:11,502 --> 00:20:13,754
<b>her instincts.</b>

288
00:20:13,796 --> 00:20:21,095
<b>♪ ♪</b>

289
00:20:23,097 --> 00:20:27,393
<b>Hakushi taught her how
to avoid taking responsibility</b>

290
00:20:27,434 --> 00:20:29,353
<b>for what she did in games.</b>

291
00:20:30,479 --> 00:20:35,943
<b>Deep inhale, deep
exhale, repeat.</b>

292
00:20:37,070 --> 00:20:39,237
<b>[breathing]</b>

293
00:20:39,279 --> 00:20:43,617
<b>But in the end,
that technique wasn't</b>

294
00:20:43,659 --> 00:20:47,413
<b>enough to clear her mind.</b>

295
00:20:48,748 --> 00:20:52,292
<b>No matter how
many breaths she took,</b>

296
00:20:52,334 --> 00:20:54,962
<b>no matter how deep,</b>

297
00:20:55,004 --> 00:20:57,590
<b>she couldn't shake it off.</b>

298
00:20:59,217 --> 00:21:02,095
<b>Yuki's heartbeat
started to feel strange,</b>

299
00:21:02,136 --> 00:21:08,226
<b>like something was stuck in it,
something sharp, like a needle.</b>

300
00:21:09,727 --> 00:21:12,063
<b>There was a part
of Yuki that couldn't</b>

301
00:21:12,105 --> 00:21:15,149
<b>accept the reality
of that Stump girl dying</b>

302
00:21:16,442 --> 00:21:19,528
<b>while she was
allowed to live.</b>

303
00:21:21,072 --> 00:21:24,491
<b>And she knew, if she
thought like that,</b>

304
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:28,495
<b>and bumped into the psycho,
she was dead.</b>

305
00:21:31,582 --> 00:21:32,959
<b>[footsteps]</b>

306
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,544
<b>But her legs didn't stop.</b>

307
00:21:35,586 --> 00:21:40,507
<b>She kept walking,
one foot after another.</b>

308
00:21:45,221 --> 00:21:47,514
<b>If I really am a ghost...</b>

309
00:21:51,435 --> 00:21:53,271
<b>why do I still have legs?</b>

310
00:21:53,311 --> 00:21:56,983
<b>[footsteps continue]</b>

311
00:21:59,193 --> 00:22:02,362
<b>[birds chirping]</b>

312
00:22:06,492 --> 00:22:10,163
<b>[eerie musical note]</b>

313
00:22:12,372 --> 00:22:15,251
<b>[KYARA]
Incredible, isn't it?</b>

314
00:22:19,964 --> 00:22:23,217
<b>[theme music]</b>

315
00:22:23,259 --> 00:22:26,137
<b>♪ ♪</b>

316
00:22:26,179 --> 00:22:28,181
<b>Welcome back, bunny.</b>

317
00:22:28,222 --> 00:22:35,479
<b>♪ ♪</b>

